Exalate is the only decentralized solution for GitHub integrations. It allows your team to bidirectionally share data and sync with other teams working on other platforms. While giving each side full control over their incoming and outgoing data.

🙅 Don't get confined by no-code solutions only.
🦸 Fully customize your sync with scripts.
💆‍♂️ Don't leave the tool you love.
🔐 Do it all in a secure way.

Supports: GitHub, GitHub Enterprise, Jira, ServiceNow, Zendesk, Azure DevOps, Salesforce...

Check out the [Exalate for Github installation video tutorial](https://youtu.be/7MRsl8gayys). 

Main features:
⚙️ Real-time synchronization
⚙️ Choose the sync direction (one or two-way)
⚙️ Sync issues across multiple systems
⚙️ Connect multiple repositories
⚙️ Set custom mappings with just a few lines of code
⚙️ Atomate with triggers based on native query language
⚙️ Use Bulk operations to sync a large number of entities at once

[Book a demo](https://bit.ly/3HOWzHu), or consult our [documentation](https://docs.exalate.com/docs).

Check your Exalate Console URL [here](https://connect.exalate.net/github/find)
